258 59 "What general formula do the above calculations in  suggest?" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 33 "That combinations of n to the 0 (" }
{TEXT 297 1 "k" }{TEXT -1 40 ") times only results in one combination.
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "2.  \+
Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use \+
Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick \+
will be to get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The Ma
ple command for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(ex
pression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with index
 i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   \+
" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "for p from 1 to 10\ndo e
xpand((a+1)^p);\nod;" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}{PARA 
